The paper discusses the impact of caching on real-time and cyber-physical systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses the required hardware and OS modifications to support the proposed cacheability control, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.OS (Operating Systems) sub-category. The paper evaluates the system on an architectural simulator, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.EM (Embedded Systems) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of data coherence on worst-case execution time, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the overall system design and control, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
